trans-unit.source: Called by an MBean server when this connector server is registered in that MBean server. This connector server becomes attached to the MBean server and its getMBeanServer() method will return mbs.
trans-unit.target: 当该连接器服务器注册在该MBean服务器中时，由MBean服务器调用。该连接器服务器将连接到MBean服务器，并且其 getMBeanServer() 方法将返回 mbs 。

trans-unit.source: Called by an MBean server when this connector server is unregistered from that MBean server. If this connector server was attached to that MBean server by being registered in it, and if the connector server is still active, then unregistering it will call the stop method. If the stop method throws an exception, the unregistration attempt will fail. It is recommended to call the stop method explicitly before unregistering the MBean.
trans-unit.target: 从该MBean服务器取消注册该连接器服务器时，由MBean服务器调用。如果此连接器服务器通过在该MBean服务器上注册而连接到该MBean服务器，并且如果该连接器服务器仍处于活动状态，则取消注册该连接器服务器将调用 stop 方法。如果 stop 方法引发异常，则注销尝试将失败。建议在注销MBean之前显式调用 stop 方法。

trans-unit.source: Called by readObject with the newly deserialized child and BCSChild.
trans-unit.target: 由readObject调用,使用新反序列化的子代和BCSChild。

trans-unit.source: Called by the Java Virtual Machine when a thread in this thread group stops because of an uncaught exception, and the thread does not have a specific Thread.UncaughtExceptionHandler installed.
trans-unit.target: 当此线程组中的线程由于未捕获的异常而停止并且该线程未安装特定的 Thread.UncaughtExceptionHandler 时，由Java虚拟机调用。

trans-unit.source: Called by the RMI runtime sometime after the runtime determines that the reference list, the list of clients referencing the remote object, becomes empty.
trans-unit.target: 在RMI运行时确定引用列表(即引用远程对象的客户端列表)变为空后的某个时候调用。

trans-unit.source: Called by the garbage collector on an object when garbage collection determines that there are no more references to the object. A subclass overrides the finalize method to dispose of system resources or to perform other cleanup.
trans-unit.target: 当垃圾回收确定不再有对该对象的引用时，由垃圾回收器在对象上调用。子类覆盖 finalize 方法以处置系统资源或执行其他清除。

trans-unit.source: Called from setBeanContext to validate (or otherwise) the pending change in the nesting BeanContext property value. Returning false will cause setBeanContext to throw PropertyVetoException.
trans-unit.target: 从setBeanContext调用,以验证(或其他)嵌套BeanContext属性值的待定变化。返回false将导致setBeanContext抛出PropertyVetoException。

trans-unit.source: Called to indicate that a connection could not be established to a proxy/socks server. An implementation of this method can temporarily remove the proxies or reorder the sequence of proxies returned by select(URI), using the address and the IOException caught when trying to connect.
trans-unit.target: 调用以指示无法建立与代理/袜子服务器的连接。此方法的实现可以使用尝试连接时捕获的地址和IOException 临时删除代理或对由 select(URI) 返回的代理序列重新排序。

trans-unit.source: Called to notify a listener of an event in the print service. The service will call this method on an event notification thread. The client should not perform lengthy processing in this callback or subsequent event notifications may be blocked.
trans-unit.target: 调用此方法是为了通知监听器打印服务中的事件。服务将在事件通知线程上调用该方法。客户端不应在此回调中执行冗长的处理,否则可能会阻止后续的事件通知。

trans-unit.source: Called to notify the client that an error has occurred that the user might be able to fix. One example of an error that can generate this event is when the printer runs out of paper.
trans-unit.target: 调用它来通知客户机发生了错误,而用户也许可以修复。一个可以产生该事件的错误的例子是当打印机用完纸的时候。

trans-unit.source: Called to notify the client that data has been successfully transferred to the print service, and the client may free local resources allocated for that data. The client should not assume that the data has been completely printed after receiving this event.
trans-unit.target: 调用该事件是为了通知客户机数据已成功传输到打印服务,客户机可以释放为该数据分配的本地资源。客户端在收到该事件后,不应认为数据已完全打印完毕。

trans-unit.source: Called to notify the client that data has been successfully transferred to the print service, and the client may free local resources allocated for that data. The client should not assume that the data has been completely printed after receiving this event. If this event is not received the client should wait for a terminal event (completed/canceled/failed) before freeing the resources.
trans-unit.target: 调用该事件是为了通知客户机数据已成功传输到打印服务,客户机可以释放为该数据分配的本地资源。客户端在收到该事件后,不应认为数据已完全打印完毕。如果没有收到该事件,客户端应在释放资源之前等待终端事件(完成/取消/失败)。

trans-unit.source: Called to notify the client that no more events will be delivered. One cause of this event being generated is if the job has successfully completed, but the printing system is limited in capability and cannot verify this. This event is required to be delivered if none of the other terminal events (completed/failed/canceled) are delivered.
trans-unit.target: 调用来通知客户端不再交付事件。产生该事件的一个原因是,如果作业已成功完成,但打印系统能力有限,无法验证。如果其他终端事件(完成/失败/取消)均未交付,则需要交付该事件。

trans-unit.source: Called to notify the client that some possibly user rectifiable problem occurs (eg printer out of paper).
trans-unit.target: 调用此功能是为了通知客户端发生了一些可能是用户可纠正的问题(如打印机缺纸)。

trans-unit.source: Called to notify the client that the job completed successfully.
trans-unit.target: 调用通知客户工作成功完成。

trans-unit.target: 用相同的参数调用此方法两次,可能返回相同的对象或两个相等但不相同的对象。

trans-unit.target: 当连接器服务器已经被停止时,调用本方法没有任何效果。当连接器服务器尚未启动时,调用本方法将永久禁用连接器服务器对象。

trans-unit.source: Channels are, in general, intended to be safe for multithreaded access as described in the specifications of the interfaces and classes that extend and implement this interface.
trans-unit.target: 一般来说,通道的目的是为了安全地进行多线程访问,这在扩展和实现该接口的接口和类的规范中有所描述。

trans-unit.source: Channels of this type are safe for use by multiple concurrent threads though at most one accept operation can be outstanding at any time. If a thread initiates an accept operation before a previous accept operation has completed then an AcceptPendingException will be thrown.
trans-unit.target: 这种类型的通道可以安全地供多个并发线程使用，尽管最多可以随时执行一个接受操作。如果线程在上一个接受操作完成之前启动了接受操作，则将引发 AcceptPendingException 。

trans-unit.source: Channels of this type are safe for use by multiple concurrent threads. The close method may be invoked at any time, as specified by the Channel interface. This causes all outstanding asynchronous operations on the channel to complete with the exception AsynchronousCloseException. Multiple read and write operations may be outstanding at the same time. When multiple read and write operations are outstanding then the ordering of the I/O operations, and the order that the completion handlers are invoked, is not specified; they are not, in particular, guaranteed to execute in the order that the operations were initiated. The ByteBuffers used when reading or writing are not safe for use by multiple concurrent I/O operations. Furthermore, after an I/O operation is initiated then care should be taken to ensure that the buffer is not accessed until after the operation has completed.
trans-unit.target: 这种类型的通道可以安全地供多个并发线程使用。如 Channel 接口所指定的， close 方法可以随时调用。这将导致通道上所有未完成的异步操作都完成，并带有 AsynchronousCloseException 异常。多个读和写操作可能同时处于未完成状态。当多个读和写操作尚未完成时，则不指定I / O操作的顺序以及完成处理程序的调用顺序。尤其不能保证它们以启动操作的顺序执行。该 ByteBuffers 在进行多个并发I / O操作不安全时进行读取或写入时使用。此外，在启动I / O操作之后，应注意确保直到操作完成后才访问缓冲区。

trans-unit.source: Channels of this type are safe for use by multiple concurrent threads. They support concurrent reading and writing, though at most one read operation and one write operation can be outstanding at any time. If a thread initiates a read operation before a previous read operation has completed then a ReadPendingException will be thrown. Similarly, an attempt to initiate a write operation before a previous write has completed will throw a WritePendingException.
trans-unit.target: 这种类型的通道可以安全地供多个并发线程使用。它们支持并发读取和写入，尽管最多可以随时执行一次读取操作和一个写入操作。如果线程在上一个读取操作完成之前启动了读取操作，则将引发 ReadPendingException 。类似地，尝试在上一次写入完成之前启动写入操作将抛出 WritePendingException 。
